f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates FET/USDT funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices over the previous period. The exchange's institutional-grade matching engine on Sui processes funding settlements with sub-second finality, eliminating the settlement delays common on other networks. Funding payments occur automatically at each hourly interval, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to 0.3% during normal market conditions. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short positions receive payments, creating clear arbitrage signals for traders monitoring cross-exchange rate differentials."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FET","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's position as a prominent AI infrastructure token makes it particularly sensitive to funding rate fluctuations during AI market cycles and major announcements. The token's mid-tier volume on Bluefin creates opportunities for informed traders to capitalize on funding rate imbalances before they normalize. Bluefin's status as the leading perpetual DEX on Sui means FET funding rates here often diverge from CEX rates due to different user bases and liquidity patterns."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET funding rates on Bluefin have historically shown strong correlation with AI sector momentum, often spiking above 0.5% during major AI announcements or partnership reveals. The hourly settlement frequency creates more granular arbitrage windows compared to 8-hour funding cycles on traditional exchanges. During the Q1 2024 AI rally, FET funding rates consistently traded at premiums to other altcoins, reflecting sustained long interest from Sui ecosystem participants. Volatility in funding rates typically increases around Fetch.ai development milestones and broader AI market catalysts."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently emerge between Bluefin's FET rates and centralized exchanges due to the distinct user demographics and trading patterns on Sui. The 0.02% maker fee structure allows profitable arbitrage even on smaller rate differentials, particularly when combined with Bluefin's fast settlement times. Traders often identify profitable spreads during Asian trading hours when Sui network activity peaks and funding rate divergences are most pronounced. The relatively lower FET volume on Bluefin compared to major CEXs can lead to sustained rate premiums lasting multiple funding periods."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's AI narrative exposure creates funding rate volatility that can quickly reverse during broader tech sector selloffs or regulatory concerns around AI development. Bluefin's position in the developing Sui ecosystem means liquidity can become constrained during market stress, potentially widening bid-ask spreads and complicating position management. Cross-chain bridge risks exist when arbitraging between Bluefin and other networks, particularly during high network congestion periods. Traders should monitor FET's correlation with major AI stocks and crypto market sentiment, as funding rates can shift rapidly during risk-off periods affecting growth narratives."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How do FET funding rates on Bluefin compare to centralized exchanges?","answer":"Bluefin's FET rates often trade at premiums to CEXs due to the Sui ecosystem's focus on infrastructure tokens and different user demographics. The hourly settlement frequency provides more arbitrage opportunities but requires active monitoring compared to 8-hour cycles elsewhere."},{"question":"What drives FET funding rate volatility on Bluefin specifically?","answer":"FET rates are particularly sensitive to AI sector developments, Fetch.ai partnership announcements, and broader Sui ecosystem growth. Bluefin's institutional-grade matching engine and professional trader base can amplify rate movements during high-conviction periods."},{"question":"Are there minimum position sizes for FET funding rate arbitrage on Bluefin?","answer":"While Bluefin doesn't enforce minimum sizes, the 0.02% maker fee structure makes positions under $10,000 less profitable for pure funding arbitrage. The exchange's low slippage environment supports larger positions without significant price impact."},{"question":"How does Sui network performance affect FET funding settlements?","answer":"Sui's high throughput and sub-second finality ensure reliable hourly funding settlements even during peak activity. The network's parallel execution capabilities prevent the congestion issues that can delay settlements on other blockchain-based derivatives platforms."}]}]
